<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 06 at 2:59PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
southwestern Campbell and south central Bedford Counties through 330
PM EDT...
At 258 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Smith Mountain Lake State Park, or 7 miles northeast of Penhook,
moving northeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Altavista...
Hurt...
Huddleston...
Leesville...
and Smith Mountain Lake State Park.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM EDT for
central, south central and west central Virginia.</instruction>
